# Python Documentation Standards

## Documentation

- Keep README files up to date
- Document any new build processes
- Update requirements.txt when adding dependencies
- Comment complex build scripts

## Agentic AI Change Summaries

- **NEVER write .md files summarizing agentic AI changes directly to the root directory**
- **Place all agentic AI change summaries in appropriate subdirectories**:
  - Development logs: `DEVELOPMENT_LOG/` directory
  - Feature documentation: `DEVELOPMENT_LOG/features/` directory
  - System documentation: `DEVELOPMENT_LOG/systems/` directory
  - Workflow documentation: `DEVELOPMENT_LOG/workflows/` directory
- **Use descriptive filenames** that indicate the nature of the changes
- **Include timestamps** in filenames when appropriate (e.g., `2025-08-28_23-15_FEATURE_NAME.md`)
- **Maintain organized structure** within the DEVELOPMENT_LOG directory

## Code Comments

- Write clear, concise comments explaining complex logic
- Use docstrings for all public functions and classes
- Follow Google or NumPy docstring conventions
- Keep comments up-to-date with code changes

## API Documentation

- Document all public interfaces clearly
- Include usage examples in docstrings
- Specify parameter types and return values
- Document any side effects or exceptions

